claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: Figure with panels A–D displaying geometric mean ratios of egg-to-cell virus titers (95% CI) and proportions of ≥4-fold reduced titers pre- and post-vaccination for four influenza vaccines (Fluzone IIV4, Fluarix IIV4, ccIIV4, RIV4) across influenza strains (A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/VIC, B/YAM) in two age groups (18–44, 45–64 years). does not support the claim because the image shows immunogenicity comparisons including RIV4 but provides no information on production platform, BEVS, or insect-cell expression of recombinant HA Note: No production or manufacturing details are visible in the figure; content is limited to virological assay results.
